You'll need node installed.
For Debian,Ubuntu :
Make sure you have installed deb package build-essential
Download node package and do configure,make,make install.
Install node from http://nodejs.org/ . You'll download a package that you
must first install with $ tar zxvf node-vX.Y.tar.gz

The download & install pegjs node package with npm globally.
$ npm -g install pegjs

If 
$ node parser.js  
throws error not finding pegjs theh supply a full path:
var PEG = require('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/pegjs');

